    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-10-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-12-13T23:01:00Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Endangered Species Act of 1973 to provide for the suspension of each provision of the Act with respect to a federal or state agency that manages a federal river basin if the Secretary of the Army (acting through the Chief of Engineers) or the governor of the relevant state determines that: (1) a drought is in effect in the region in which the basin is located; and (2) such drought presents a threat to the health, safety, or welfare of the region's population. Terminates such a suspension on the date the Secretary or governor determines the drought is no longer in effect.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
